President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed April 2018 as National Child Abuse Prevention Month in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of providing a safe and nurturing environment for every child and highlights the negative consequences of child abuse and neglect. It calls upon Americans to be aware of the signs of child abuse and to take action to protect children in need. The proclamation also recognizes the professionals, volunteers, and organizations working to protect at-risk children and care for those who have experienced abuse or neglect. President Trump encourages all Americans to support efforts that promote the psychological, physical, and emotional development of children.